{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"ResizeObserverEntry.borderBoxSize","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ResizeObserverEntry/borderBoxSize","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Resize_Observer_API\">Resize Observer API</a></strong></li><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ResizeObserverEntry\"><code>ResizeObserverEntry</code></a></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Properties</summary><ol><li><em><code>borderBoxSize</code></em></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ResizeObserverEntry/contentBoxSize\"><code>contentBoxSize</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ResizeObserverEntry/contentRect\"><code>contentRect</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ResizeObserverEntry/devicePixelContentBoxSize\"><code>devicePixelContentBoxSize</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ResizeObserverEntry/target\"><code>target</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Related pages for Resize Observer API</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ResizeObserver\"><code>ResizeObserver</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>\n  The <strong><code>borderBoxSize</code></strong> read-only property of\n  the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ResizeObserverEntry\"><code>ResizeObserverEntry</code></a> interface returns an array containing the new\n  border box size of the observed element when the callback is run.\n</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"value","title":"Value","isH3":false,"content":"<p>\n  An array containing objects with the new border box size of the observed element. The\n  array is necessary to support elements that have multiple fragments, which occur in\n  multi-column scenarios. Each object in the array contains two properties:\n</p>\n<dl>\n  <dt id=\"blocksize\"><code>blockSize</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>\n      The length of the observed element's border box in the block dimension. For boxes\n      with a horizontal <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/writing-mode\"><code>writing-mode</code></a>, this is the vertical dimension, or\n      height; if the writing-mode is vertical, this is the horizontal dimension, or width.\n    </p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"inlinesize\"><code>inlineSize</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>\n      The length of the observed element's border box in the inline dimension. For boxes\n      with a horizontal <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/writing-mode\"><code>writing-mode</code></a>, this is the horizontal dimension, or\n      width; if the writing-mode is vertical, this is the vertical dimension, or height.\n    </p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>\n<div class=\"notecard note\" id=\"sect1\">\n  <p>\n    <strong>Note:</strong> For more explanation of writing modes and block and inline\n    dimensions, read <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Learn/CSS/Building_blocks/Handling_different_text_directions\">Handling\ndifferent text directions</a>.\n  </p>\n</div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> resizeObserver <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">ResizeObserver</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">entries</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">for</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> entry <span class=\"token keyword\">of</span> entries<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">if</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>entry<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>borderBoxSize <span class=\"token operator\">&amp;&amp;</span> entry<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>borderBoxSize<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>length <span class=\"token operator\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      entry<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>target<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>style<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>borderRadius <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> Math<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">min</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">100</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>entry<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>borderBoxSize<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>inlineSize<span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token number\">10</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">+</span>\n                                                      <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>entry<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>borderBoxSize<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>blockSize<span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token number\">10</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">+</span> <span class=\"token string\">'px'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">else</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      entry<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>target<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>style<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>borderRadius <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> Math<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">min</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">100</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>entry<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>contentRect<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>width<span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token number\">10</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">+</span>\n                                                      <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>entry<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>contentRect<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>height<span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token number\">10</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">+</span> <span class=\"token string\">'px'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\nresizeObserver<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">observe</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>document<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">querySelector</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'div'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://drafts.csswg.org/resize-observer/#dom-resizeobserverentry-borderboxsize","title":"Resize Observer"}],"query":"api.ResizeObserverEntry.borderBoxSize"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.ResizeObserverEntry.borderBoxSize","dataURL":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ResizeObserverEntry/borderBoxSize/bcd.json"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Value","id":"value"},{"text":"Examples","id":"examples"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"}],"summary":"The borderBoxSize read-only property of\n  the ResizeObserverEntry interface returns an array containing the new\n  border box size of the observed element when the callback is run.","popularity":0.0008,"modified":"2022-02-18T09:26:54.000Z","source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/resizeobserverentry/borderboxsize","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/api/resizeobserverentry/borderboxsize/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/93ae23dec42bba9d71d6f1ed45668d8d26847e9c","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ResizeObserverEntry","title":"ResizeObserverEntry"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ResizeObserverEntry/borderBoxSize","title":"ResizeObserverEntry.borderBoxSize"}],"pageTitle":"ResizeObserverEntry.borderBoxSize - Web APIs | MDN","noIndexing":false}}